      "content": "okay but if it's that \"problematic,\" why is it still being pushed as this big moral good by most mainstream institutions and media? it feels like there isn't even a real debate anymore because anyone who points out the censorship gets labeled as the bad guy. doesn't that make the whole thing more of a political tool than an actual movement for justice?",
